The Chronicle Al Ahly head coach Pitso Mosimane has tested positive for the Covid-19, the club have confirmed. The new Egyptian Premier League just got underway last weekend, with Mosimane’s side picking up a 3-1 win over Misr Lel Makkasa. The Red Devils have now confirmed that the former Mamelodi Sundowns head coach will self-isolate after testing positive for the virus. The club’s statement read: Al Ahly’s head coach Pitso Mosimane tested positive for COVID-19. Mosimane will be subjected to the home isolation regime, set by the Ministry of Health. As a result, Mosimane will now miss Friday’s league clash against Ghazl El Mahalla. 